03:43.058 --> 03:45.015
<i>♪ Raised by wolves ♪</i>

03:45.040 --> 03:47.245
<i>♪ Independent... ♪</i>

03:47.290 --> 03:49.884
- Have you touched anything?
- Only the recorder.

03:49.909 --> 03:52.379
<i>♪ Civilized but ♪</i>

03:52.380 --> 03:54.029
<i>♪ A little restless ♪</i>

03:54.054 --> 03:55.829
<i>♪ Don't test my skills ♪</i>

03:55.830 --> 03:57.499
<i>♪ Don't doubt my bones ♪</i>

03:57.500 --> 03:58.842
<i>♪ Raised by wolves... ♪</i>

03:58.867 --> 04:00.459
- [door creaks]
- [wind rushes in]

04:00.460 --> 04:03.079
BRIGID: Get out of here.
I have a mess to clean up.

04:03.080 --> 04:04.789
- Brigid...
- If you don't leave now,

04:04.790 --> 04:06.749
I'm gonna arrest both of you myself.

04:06.750 --> 04:08.959
<i>♪ A little restless ♪</i>

04:08.960 --> 04:10.749
<i>♪ Don't test my skills ♪</i>

04:10.750 --> 04:12.960
<i>♪ Don't pick my brain ♪</i>

04:17.504 --> 04:21.137
<i>♪ I need your love ♪</i>

04:21.209 --> 04:24.129
<i>♪ I need your love ♪</i>

04:25.460 --> 04:27.169
Hey, she's got her own issues.

04:27.170 --> 04:29.879
- She didn't mean anything...
- What she meant was pretty clear.

04:29.880 --> 04:32.329
All this... all this is on me.

04:32.330 --> 04:33.959
Or, it's on them.

04:33.960 --> 04:35.539
Who?

04:35.540 --> 04:37.000
All those people in the club.

04:38.120 --> 04:39.919
A lot of them buy from those gangs, Ty,

04:39.920 --> 04:41.329
and they'll do it tomorrow, too.

04:41.330 --> 04:43.419
No matter how much you steal,

04:43.420 --> 04:45.709
no matter how many dealers drop dead

04:45.710 --> 04:48.619
- everybody plays their part.
- Tandy, you can't blame people...

04:48.620 --> 04:49.919
And why not?

04:49.920 --> 04:51.942
Why not? Those people choose misery

04:51.967 --> 04:53.233
and I'm sick of watching it.

04:53.257 --> 04:56.145
People don't... choose
to struggle, Tandy.

04:56.170 --> 04:57.790
They don't choose the hurt.

04:59.880 --> 05:02.829
Doing nothing is not a solution.

05:02.830 --> 05:04.456
<i>♪ Take you down ♪</i>

05:04.481 --> 05:06.249
<i>♪ Underrated ♪</i>

05:06.250 --> 05:07.425
<i>♪ Trained in the wild ♪</i>

05:07.450 --> 05:11.499
<i>♪ I'm back for answers,
back for the crown ♪</i>

05:11.500 --> 05:14.710
♪♪

05:18.500 --> 05:20.083
[knocking at door]

05:22.490 --> 05:23.830
Come in, Tyrone.

05:25.880 --> 05:28.789
- How'd you know it was me?
- Goat ankle bones.

05:29.126 --> 05:30.360
Seriously?

05:35.077 --> 05:37.058
So, what has you walkin'
through my store

05:37.083 --> 05:38.374
like a sinner through church?

05:38.647 --> 05:40.881
Evita's out giving a tour.

05:42.014 --> 05:43.543
I'm actually here to see you.

05:45.080 --> 05:46.709
What about?

05:46.710 --> 05:48.249
Well, I, um...

05:48.250 --> 05:49.879
I saw something...

05:49.880 --> 05:52.620
a pattern, I-I remembered
seeing it in front of the shop.

05:54.190 --> 05:55.850
That is a veve.

05:56.940 --> 06:00.791
A veve is a... an invocation.

06:00.850 --> 06:03.899
A kind of... transactional prayer.

06:03.900 --> 06:07.519
A method used for summoning
so a question can be asked.

06:07.520 --> 06:08.899
A request made.

06:08.900 --> 06:10.769
Summoning what?

06:10.863 --> 06:12.863
A Loa.

06:14.400 --> 06:15.979
The Greeks have their gods.

06:15.980 --> 06:18.059
The Catholics their saints.

06:18.060 --> 06:19.849
We have the Loa.

06:19.850 --> 06:22.059
And each Loa has their own veve,

06:22.060 --> 06:23.399
particular to them.

06:23.400 --> 06:26.059
And each line, each symbol...

06:26.060 --> 06:27.939
- it has a meaning.
- And, uh, this...

06:27.940 --> 06:29.269
this-this veve, it's...

06:29.270 --> 06:32.019
It belongs to Maman Brigitte.

06:32.020 --> 06:33.439
One of the death Loa.

06:33.440 --> 06:36.939
- I'm sorry, death Loa?
- [Auntie laughs]

06:36.940 --> 06:40.149
Death isn't a bad thing, Tyrone.

06:40.150 --> 06:42.609
Not the way the Voudon see the world.

06:42.610 --> 06:44.399
It's simply a path we must all walk

06:44.400 --> 06:45.899
to reunite with our ancestors.

06:45.900 --> 06:47.729
Yeah, I think the guy who drew this,

06:47.730 --> 06:50.796
- he knew he was gonna die.
- Which means one of two things.

06:50.821 --> 06:52.979
He either wanted to be guided
from this life to the next,

06:52.980 --> 06:55.108
or... he wants justice.

06:55.133 --> 06:56.479
Justice?

06:56.480 --> 06:59.149
Maman Brigitte can be a powerful ally.

06:59.150 --> 07:01.850
For justice... or revenge.

07:04.407 --> 07:06.446
What's going on with you, boy?

07:06.471 --> 07:08.899
Go on, spill it.

07:08.900 --> 07:11.980
I don't know how to... [sighs]

07:13.810 --> 07:16.189
[scoffs] Look, I'm trying to help.

07:16.190 --> 07:18.019
To fix things in any way I can.

07:18.020 --> 07:21.060
But every thing I try,
every time I try...

07:22.494 --> 07:24.034
I make it worse.

07:26.400 --> 07:28.704
I-I don't know what to do.

07:29.805 --> 07:31.825
Perhaps you should pray on it.

07:31.850 --> 07:33.769
Yeah. 'Cause that always works...

07:33.770 --> 07:35.399
Uh-uh...

07:35.400 --> 07:37.939
Don't bring that narrow-minded
nonsense up in here.

07:37.940 --> 07:40.019
What do you think happens when you pray?

07:40.020 --> 07:42.809
Who do you think you're praying to?

07:42.810 --> 07:45.810
Well, I don't know...
that's the problem.

07:47.440 --> 07:48.980
You have a wounded soul.

07:49.005 --> 07:51.269
All that you've been through.

07:51.270 --> 07:53.238
But if you let those
wounds become scars,

07:53.263 --> 07:54.849
you're gonna look at yourself one day

07:54.850 --> 07:56.439
and not recognize what you see.

07:56.440 --> 07:57.769
You think I don't know that?

07:57.770 --> 07:59.809
I'm trying.

07:59.810 --> 08:01.619
But I-I can't talk to my parents.

08:01.644 --> 08:03.524
My friends think I'm toxic.

08:05.302 --> 08:06.392
And Evita, I...

08:07.900 --> 08:10.269
God... the universe...

08:11.189 --> 08:12.729
whatever you want to call it...

08:12.730 --> 08:15.609
the answers aren't out there, Tyrone.

08:15.610 --> 08:19.149
Not in your parents, or
your friends, or Evita,

08:19.150 --> 08:20.399
or me.

08:20.400 --> 08:23.725
All the power of the universe is in here.

08:23.770 --> 08:26.439
Prayer, when you do it right,

08:26.440 --> 08:28.309
is a way to quiet the mind.

08:28.310 --> 08:31.343
So your soul can be heard.

08:31.520 --> 08:33.610
The answers lie inside of you.

08:35.770 --> 08:37.109
So...

08:37.110 --> 08:38.650
what do you want to ask?

08:40.559 --> 08:42.399
Are you making a veve?

08:43.047 --> 08:46.649
- Whose is it?
- Most know him as Papa Legba.

08:46.650 --> 08:48.439
Keeper of the Crossroads.

08:48.440 --> 08:50.979
I'm gonna ask him to protect you.

08:50.980 --> 08:52.849
From what?

08:52.951 --> 08:55.877
EVITA: Please, Auntie, tell me
those are biscuits I smell.

08:57.850 --> 08:59.400
Hey, Evita.

09:03.917 --> 09:05.746
[door slams shut]

09:05.771 --> 09:06.958
Evita!

09:06.982 --> 09:09.165
[sighs] Eight months, Tyrone,
eight months!

09:09.190 --> 09:10.761
Look, I know, I know, and I'm sorry...

09:10.809 --> 09:13.519
Even after I saw that mark
on your arm, I believed.

09:13.520 --> 09:16.802
Okay? Against all I was raised
to believe, I believed in you.

09:16.827 --> 09:19.439
I mean, when... when your body
wasn't found, I thought, good,

09:19.440 --> 09:21.649
you know, good, maybe he...
maybe he's just laying low.

09:21.650 --> 09:24.198
I mean, as soon as he's able to let
me know he's all right, he will.

09:24.223 --> 09:26.309
- Evita, I...
- Every day.

09:26.310 --> 09:27.809
Every week.

09:27.810 --> 09:30.439
Every month I tried,
Tyrone, I tried so hard

09:30.440 --> 09:32.689
to keep my mind from
going to dark places.

09:32.690 --> 09:34.271
Okay? The worst places.

09:34.296 --> 09:36.649
I tried everything.

09:36.650 --> 09:38.479
Only thing that worked?

09:38.480 --> 09:40.609
I had to convince myself
that you had forgotten me.

09:40.610 --> 09:43.229
That you didn't care about me.

09:43.230 --> 09:44.689
You know why?

09:44.690 --> 09:46.754
Cause that was better than
thinking that you were dead.

09:46.779 --> 09:47.848
It's not that simple.

09:47.898 --> 09:49.873
There's a whole police department
out there looking for me.

09:49.898 --> 09:52.399
- Any contact would be dangerous...
- Yeah?! What about now?

09:52.400 --> 09:53.944
I mean, a-a-all of a sudden it's okay

09:53.969 --> 09:55.397
for you to be out in broad daylight?

09:55.422 --> 09:57.381
'Cause that's where you are, Tyrone.
So, why now?

09:57.382 --> 09:59.328
I had to ask your Aunt a
question about Voudon, and...

09:59.353 --> 10:02.006
Wait, wait, so it wasn't even to see me?

10:02.031 --> 10:04.950
- You wanted to know about Voudon?
- No, that's not...

10:04.951 --> 10:07.410
[sighs] Look, I-I mean,
it is why I'm here,

10:07.411 --> 10:09.281
but it's because people are getting...

10:10.685 --> 10:13.644
I opened the can of worms
and people got hurt.

10:13.911 --> 10:15.534
So once you got your questions,
you were gonna what?

10:15.621 --> 10:17.994
Just let me continue to
worry about you?!

10:18.056 --> 10:19.214
No, that's not... Evita!

10:19.275 --> 10:20.660
You have nothing to worry about!

10:20.661 --> 10:22.120
- The police can't catch me.
- [chuckles] Come on.

10:22.121 --> 10:23.538
The police can catch all of us.

10:23.563 --> 10:25.069
You, out of anybody, should know that.

10:25.094 --> 10:26.780
Look, I know, that's not what I meant.

10:26.781 --> 10:28.030
So, what do you mean?

10:28.031 --> 10:30.200
I mean that there
are things that I can do.

10:30.201 --> 10:31.926
What are you talking about?

10:36.991 --> 10:39.241
Look, come on... Come on!

10:42.831 --> 10:45.620
♪ ♪

10:45.621 --> 10:47.161
All right, here should be good.

10:49.201 --> 10:50.491
You ready?

10:51.531 --> 10:52.831
For what?

10:58.071 --> 11:00.870
Did I just... Did you just...

11:00.871 --> 11:03.831
- That's... that's what I can do.
- How did you ju...

11:05.911 --> 11:08.990
Okay, how long have you
been able to do that?

11:08.991 --> 11:10.620
It all started around state semis,

11:10.621 --> 11:13.160
but I got, you know,
better at controlling it

11:13.161 --> 11:15.039
around the time the city went crazy.

11:15.064 --> 11:18.911
So like, eight months ago?

11:22.031 --> 11:24.450
Are you serious?!
You're telling me you could just...

11:24.451 --> 11:25.740
do that this entire time?

11:25.741 --> 11:27.862
And you didn't think to come
and tell me you were safe?!

11:27.887 --> 11:29.957
- Evita, I...
- Tyrone, no!

11:29.988 --> 11:32.570
Just... no.

11:32.571 --> 11:34.330
♪ ♪

11:34.331 --> 11:36.030
<i>♪ Just another one-night stand ♪</i>

11:36.031 --> 11:37.910
<i>♪ Anything to feel something ♪</i>

11:37.911 --> 11:39.654
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm just so numb without you ♪</i>

11:39.679 --> 11:41.941
<i>♪ Anything, I just gotta
feel something ♪</i>

11:41.966 --> 11:45.660
<i>♪ Yeah we gotta deal with things
in life to find the one thing ♪</i>

11:45.661 --> 11:47.870
<i>♪ Now I'm huntin' for the
one change to function ♪</i>

11:47.871 --> 11:49.616
<i>♪ Or the situation
that the love brings ♪</i>

11:49.641 --> 11:51.870
<i>♪ But the situation, not the
reason, I decide to be ♪</i>

11:51.871 --> 11:53.780
<i>♪ This one-on-one thing ♪</i>

11:53.781 --> 11:55.370
<i>♪ If I die today ♪</i>

11:55.371 --> 11:57.410
<i>♪ I would get my way ♪</i>

11:57.411 --> 12:00.160
<i>♪ But I need you more than
I need myself I cannot fake ♪</i>

12:00.161 --> 12:01.740
<i>♪ No I can't hide the fact... ♪</i>

12:01.741 --> 12:03.660
[exhales]

12:03.661 --> 12:05.242
<i>♪ Now we send a message right away ♪</i>

12:05.267 --> 12:07.490
<i>♪ Put a penny to her name... ♪</i>

12:07.491 --> 12:09.281
I want justice, too.

12:11.831 --> 12:13.241
Please.

12:14.485 --> 12:15.636
I wanna help.

12:15.707 --> 12:18.950
<i>♪ I need you like you need the sun ♪</i>

12:18.951 --> 12:21.740
<i>♪ I'm just so numb without you... ♪</i>

12:21.741 --> 12:23.621
[rattling]

12:25.781 --> 12:27.070
[panting]

12:27.071 --> 12:28.161
Help me.

12:29.192 --> 12:32.682
Please... they drugged me and
I don't know where they're taking me.

12:32.812 --> 12:34.401
You gotta get me out of here.

12:34.449 --> 12:36.859
[breathing heavily]

12:38.411 --> 12:40.160
- [Tyrone shushing]
- [Mikayla panting]

12:40.161 --> 12:42.870
[Mikayla whimpering]

12:42.871 --> 12:44.031
[panting]

12:46.363 --> 12:47.948
PASSENGER: Hey! What the
hell are you doing?!

12:47.973 --> 12:50.433
- Please, please, get me out of here!
- I'm trying, I'm trying!

12:52.184 --> 12:54.183
- I'm gonna try to...
- [gun cocks]

12:54.263 --> 12:56.182
[gunfire]

12:56.183 --> 12:58.972
<i>♪ Cause I'm just so numb without you ♪</i>

12:58.973 --> 13:02.392
<i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>

13:02.393 --> 13:05.972
<i>♪ I'm just, I'm just
so numb without you ♪</i>

13:05.973 --> 13:09.892
<i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>

13:09.893 --> 13:12.063
<i>♪ Cause I'm just so numb without you ♪</i>

13:16.893 --> 13:18.972
- [door creaks]
- [wind rushes in]

13:18.973 --> 13:19.893
BRIGID: Get out of here.

13:19.894 --> 13:21.682
I have a mess to clean up.

13:21.683 --> 13:23.229
- TYRONE: Brigid...
- BRIGID: If you don't leave now,

13:23.254 --> 13:25.294
I'm gonna arrest both of you myself.

13:27.659 --> 13:29.121
TANDY: She didn't mean anything
by what she...

13:29.145 --> 13:31.392
TYRONE: No. It's pretty clear
what she meant.

13:31.393 --> 13:34.640
All this... it's on me.

13:34.665 --> 13:36.584
Or it's on them.

13:36.609 --> 13:37.728
Who?

13:37.753 --> 13:39.752
Those people in the club.

13:39.777 --> 13:41.819
A lot of them buy from those gangs, Ty,

13:41.844 --> 13:43.843
and they'll do it tomorrow, too.

13:43.868 --> 13:45.129
No matter how much you steal.

13:45.154 --> 13:47.660
No matter how many dealers drop dead.

13:47.723 --> 13:49.012
Everybody plays their part.

13:49.013 --> 13:51.102
- Tandy, you can't blame people for...
- And why not?

13:51.511 --> 13:53.667
Why not? Those people choose misery.

13:53.692 --> 13:54.863
And I'm sick of watching it.

13:54.888 --> 13:57.019
People don't choose to struggle, Tandy.

13:57.768 --> 13:59.347
They don't choose the hurt.

13:59.473 --> 14:01.531
Doing nothing is not a solution.

14:01.556 --> 14:04.512
Like Brigid said, we're
not helping anything, Ty.

14:04.513 --> 14:05.745
We're not doing any good!

14:05.770 --> 14:07.753
And maybe people don't want to be saved.

14:07.778 --> 14:09.229
By us, or at all.

14:11.071 --> 14:13.126
MIKAYLA: Look. I'm not kidding myself.

14:13.151 --> 14:16.594
He's hurt me. And I'm not
pretending like it didn't happen.

14:16.665 --> 14:18.574
But Jeremy knows he was wrong.

14:18.599 --> 14:20.398
He said that?

14:20.399 --> 14:21.808
MIKAYLA: And he said
he's gonna ask around

14:21.809 --> 14:23.516
for names of counselors.

14:23.541 --> 14:25.518
That he knows he might need help.

14:25.519 --> 14:27.188
LIA: Well, that sounds like
progress, but, Mikayla,

14:27.189 --> 14:29.728
we talked about how important it
is for you to stay on track...

14:29.729 --> 14:31.438
MIKAYLA: I told Jeremy
that I'm in therapy.

14:31.439 --> 14:33.768
How much it's helping me.

14:33.769 --> 14:37.689
And he said I absolutely need
to keep working on myself.

14:38.689 --> 14:40.099
He totally supports it.

14:41.309 --> 14:44.048
LIA: I think retaining your
independence is important as well.

14:44.073 --> 14:46.034
You should think about staying
at your friend's longer

14:46.104 --> 14:47.808
before moving back home.

14:47.950 --> 14:49.829
Jeremy says it's better if I move home.

14:49.854 --> 14:51.978
That being away from him for so long

14:51.979 --> 14:53.978
- is what winds him up.
- And, what?

14:53.979 --> 14:56.565
You're gonna take life advice
from the guy who hits you? [scoffs]

14:56.644 --> 14:59.173
- Is nobody here gonna call bullshit?!
- Tandy...

14:59.198 --> 15:01.683
LIA: We're not here to
offer judgment on anyone.

15:01.684 --> 15:03.601
We're here to listen,
and offer guidance.

15:03.626 --> 15:05.857
Well, your guidance has her
going back to that creep.

15:05.882 --> 15:07.263
What's the point of this

15:07.264 --> 15:08.390
if you're not gonna tell her the truth?

15:08.415 --> 15:10.223
I'm trying to figure things out.

15:10.224 --> 15:12.893
Well, why don't you figure this out...

15:12.894 --> 15:14.433
he hits you, you leave.

15:15.197 --> 15:16.901
And anything else is a choice.

15:16.934 --> 15:19.103
It's your choice!

15:19.104 --> 15:20.143
Just leave!

15:20.144 --> 15:22.763
It's not that hard, you
just get up, you walk out,

15:22.764 --> 15:24.748
and you never look back!

15:24.796 --> 15:27.846
[Katie Garfield
"I Know Your Secrets" plays]

15:30.604 --> 15:31.844
LIA: Mikayla!

15:32.650 --> 15:33.739
[door closes]

15:33.764 --> 15:39.467
<i>♪ You stand and watch the motion ♪</i>

15:39.604 --> 15:44.950
<i>♪ Watching from on high ♪</i>

15:45.208 --> 15:49.856
<i>♪ Cutting all your treasures... ♪</i>

15:49.934 --> 15:51.173
MELISSA: <i>What the hell was that?!</i>

15:51.198 --> 15:53.609
TANDY: <i>She needed to hear it!
Come on, Mom,</i>

15:53.634 --> 15:55.723
it's like she's volunteering
to get hit again.

15:55.724 --> 15:57.393
MELISSA: <i>And where do
you think she is now?</i>

15:57.394 --> 15:59.723
<i>I bet you she's at home
with that boyfriend of hers.</i>

15:59.724 --> 16:00.893
TANDY: <i>She was gonna go back, anyway.</i>

16:00.894 --> 16:01.876
MELISSA: <i>Probably.</i>

16:01.901 --> 16:03.393
But now, he doesn't even have to try

16:03.394 --> 16:05.263
to isolate her, you did it for him!

16:05.264 --> 16:08.183
[power flickering]

16:08.208 --> 16:09.503
JEREMY: <i>I don't know where Mikayla is.</i>

16:09.528 --> 16:10.644
TANDY: <i>You sure about that?</i>

16:10.669 --> 16:12.049
<i>Cause I talked to her friend Grace.</i>

16:12.074 --> 16:13.338
JEREMY: <i>Trust me, all right?</i>

16:13.363 --> 16:15.683
Bitch has my red El Cam. Thing's
worth more than she is.

16:15.684 --> 16:17.517
You find her, tell her
there's gonna be hell to pay

16:17.542 --> 16:18.933
if she doesn't return it.

16:18.934 --> 16:21.550
- [power flickering]
<i>- ♪ I know your secrets ♪</i>

16:21.575 --> 16:23.803
TANDY: <i>Yeah, you've been
on quite the streak, huh?</i>

16:23.804 --> 16:25.763
Mikayla told me about
the guys that broke in

16:25.764 --> 16:26.803
and tore up your place.

16:26.804 --> 16:28.723
There were three of 'em.

16:28.724 --> 16:29.803
But, I handled it.

16:30.811 --> 16:33.061
TANDY: <i>It's impressive.</i>

16:33.360 --> 16:34.390
<i>Especially for a guy</i>

16:34.439 --> 16:35.934
who drools when he's passed out...

16:36.704 --> 16:38.473
...and after six beers.

16:38.474 --> 16:41.013
Tough... tough guy.

16:41.014 --> 16:45.685
<i>♪ I know your secrets ♪</i>

16:45.764 --> 16:48.911
<i>♪ I know where you keep them... ♪</i>

16:48.974 --> 16:51.723
[inaudible]

16:51.724 --> 16:53.394
[power flickering]

16:55.894 --> 16:59.343
[lights emit ringing sound]

16:59.344 --> 17:01.894
[ringing gets louder]

17:04.223 --> 17:06.473
- [power blows out]
- [Tandy grunts]

17:08.394 --> 17:11.684
[panting]

17:13.000 --> 17:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

17:22.844 --> 17:25.393
- Next meeting's at six.
- Has Mikayla been back?

17:25.492 --> 17:28.571
Even if she had, the last thing
I'd do is let you talk to her.

17:28.597 --> 17:31.603
- She never went home.
- I thought that's what you wanted.

17:31.604 --> 17:33.553
Can you stop telling
me what a bitch I am

17:33.554 --> 17:35.463
and listen to me? Something is wrong!

17:35.488 --> 17:37.424
Ladies, it's getting
a little loud in here.

17:37.449 --> 17:38.604
Is everything okay?

17:38.605 --> 17:40.393
Fallout from some amateur counseling.

17:40.995 --> 17:42.778
Maybe I can help.

17:50.724 --> 17:52.643
I'm Andre Deschaine.

17:52.644 --> 17:54.513
I run the outreach programs here.

17:54.514 --> 17:57.763
- I'm... Tandy Bowen.
- I know.

17:57.764 --> 17:58.986
So, Mikayla...

17:59.011 --> 18:00.973
you know, when she
finally left her abuser,

18:00.974 --> 18:02.643
she went to stay with a friend.

18:02.644 --> 18:04.603
- I might have the number...
- Grace.

18:04.604 --> 18:06.893
Yeah, she works at Cafe du Monde.
I already talked to her.

18:06.894 --> 18:08.393
She hasn't seen Mikayla.

18:08.394 --> 18:10.553
Well, Lia was wrong about one point.

18:10.554 --> 18:12.103
She said you barely
paid attention in group,

18:12.104 --> 18:13.763
and, clearly, the opposite is true.

18:13.764 --> 18:15.103
If she's been gone all night,

18:15.128 --> 18:16.843
she could be anywhere by now.

18:16.844 --> 18:19.596
Our incoming clients get
information on Cascia House,

18:19.621 --> 18:21.290
a shelter in the Upper 9th.

18:21.291 --> 18:23.490
Mikayla would know it
was a safe place to go?

18:23.491 --> 18:25.371
Maybe your words did the trick.

18:27.371 --> 18:29.991
[men talking, laughing]

18:32.661 --> 18:35.200
So you're, like, Mr. Popularity.

18:35.201 --> 18:37.450
I spend a lot of time
in this part of town.

18:37.451 --> 18:38.620
Why's that?

18:39.890 --> 18:42.476
Sometimes people don't
know how to ask for help.

18:42.621 --> 18:43.910
So you spend time with them,

18:43.911 --> 18:45.410
get to know 'em,

18:45.411 --> 18:46.904
sometimes, small miracles can happen.

18:46.929 --> 18:48.910
Yeah, if you believe
in that sort of thing.

18:48.911 --> 18:50.580
You don't?

18:50.581 --> 18:52.790
I lived in an abandoned
church for years,

18:52.791 --> 18:54.290
and still somehow escaped

18:54.291 --> 18:56.790
- unmolested by spirituality.
- [Andre chuckles]

18:56.791 --> 18:58.200
How 'bout you?

18:58.201 --> 19:00.120
You don't seem like the godly type.

19:00.145 --> 19:03.525
I was a jazz musician,
damn good one, too.

19:03.579 --> 19:05.970
Buzz around town was
I was the next big name

19:05.994 --> 19:07.290
to come out of Frenchman Street.

19:07.291 --> 19:08.990
So what happened?

19:08.991 --> 19:11.080
Drugs, alcohol, or women?

19:11.081 --> 19:12.660
It was migraines.

19:12.661 --> 19:15.620
So bad I could barely draw a breath.

19:15.621 --> 19:16.750
It's kinda hard to blow a horn

19:16.751 --> 19:18.160
when the vibration from the note

19:18.161 --> 19:20.250
- knocks you on your ass.
- That's harsh.

19:20.251 --> 19:21.790
Brutal.

19:21.791 --> 19:24.120
And I took it out on the world.

19:24.121 --> 19:25.871
All bitterness and rage.

19:27.491 --> 19:30.080
Then you found "New Andre" and...

19:30.081 --> 19:32.200
put him on the straight and narrow.

19:32.201 --> 19:33.910
Nope.

19:33.911 --> 19:36.790
I met someone in more pain than me.

19:36.791 --> 19:39.250
A young woman who needed my help.

19:39.251 --> 19:42.201
So, I reached out and to my
surprise, it made a difference.

19:43.411 --> 19:45.490
All that misery I endured,

19:45.491 --> 19:48.384
it gave me an appreciation
for other people's suffering.

19:49.189 --> 19:50.916
Now that you know mine,

19:51.517 --> 19:53.720
- tell me yours.
- [scoffs]

19:53.745 --> 19:55.660
So, why are you here
looking for Mikayla?

19:55.661 --> 19:57.830
If you're of the mind that
people only do good things

19:57.831 --> 19:59.410
for selfish reasons...

19:59.411 --> 20:00.950
what's your angle here?

20:00.951 --> 20:02.870
MAN: Hi, Pumpkin.

20:02.871 --> 20:05.751
[heartbeat]

20:08.791 --> 20:11.990
[beating gets faster]

20:11.991 --> 20:15.410
[power surges]

20:15.411 --> 20:18.041
[power blows out, glass shatters]

20:22.161 --> 20:23.846
[distorted] What?

20:24.975 --> 20:26.160
What happened?

20:26.161 --> 20:28.648
♪ ♪

20:28.679 --> 20:30.290
Tandy?

20:30.291 --> 20:32.621
♪ ♪

20:40.949 --> 20:44.039
[indistinct bar chatter]

20:45.679 --> 20:49.080
May we get what we want.
May we get what we need.

20:49.081 --> 20:51.411
But may we never get what we deserve.

20:55.831 --> 20:57.951
[sighs]

21:00.451 --> 21:02.621
[cellphone vibrates]

21:16.581 --> 21:18.831
[cellphone vibrates]

21:23.079 --> 21:24.830
Detective O'Reilly.

21:24.831 --> 21:28.291
[muffled dance music playing]

21:35.443 --> 21:38.322
- Have you touched anything?
- Only the recorder.

21:45.912 --> 21:48.041
- [door creaks]
- [wind rushes in]

21:48.066 --> 21:49.197
Get out of here.

21:49.223 --> 21:50.769
I have a mess to clean up.

22:02.028 --> 22:04.068
[breathing heavily]

22:07.825 --> 22:10.324
[panting]

22:10.349 --> 22:11.468
[line ringing]

22:11.493 --> 22:13.656
DISPATCHER [over the phone]: <i>Hotline.</i>

22:14.223 --> 22:16.512
I need to make a report.

22:16.568 --> 22:19.394
There's several dead bodies
inside the Club Rougarou.

22:19.448 --> 22:21.158
DISPATCHER: <i>And who are you?</i>

22:23.277 --> 22:24.987
I'm nobody.

22:29.948 --> 22:33.027
♪ ♪

22:33.052 --> 22:35.092
[phone vibrates]

22:40.818 --> 22:42.907
Another.

22:42.932 --> 22:46.221
♪♪

22:46.246 --> 22:49.075
<i>♪ It just took one look ♪</i>

22:49.121 --> 22:51.701
<i>♪ And you pulled me right in ♪</i>

22:52.741 --> 22:56.362
<i>♪ If pleasure and pain ♪</i>

22:56.451 --> 22:59.080
<i>♪ Mixed lies with the truth ♪</i>

22:59.081 --> 23:04.410
[retching]

23:04.411 --> 23:06.672
[breathing heavily]

23:06.697 --> 23:08.610
Pathetic.

23:09.427 --> 23:11.157
Look at yourself.

23:11.331 --> 23:12.766
Look at yourself!

23:12.831 --> 23:15.946
Just absolutely pathetic.

23:16.041 --> 23:18.649
- Who are you?
- I always knew that you were weak.

23:18.741 --> 23:21.461
Just a scared girl,
pretending to be brave.

23:21.506 --> 23:23.875
Pretending to be police.

23:24.341 --> 23:26.340
Well, you've had your chance.

23:26.427 --> 23:28.141
It's my turn now.

23:28.241 --> 23:31.371
[loud dance music]

23:44.863 --> 23:46.282
HARD-ASS 1: O'Reilly.

23:46.331 --> 23:47.849
You better watch your back.

23:47.911 --> 23:49.677
Watch commander's pissed
about you ducking her calls.

23:49.741 --> 23:51.294
You two got a plausible story, yet?

23:51.371 --> 23:53.790
It's not that hard to figure out.
No guns allowed.

23:53.791 --> 23:54.966
Things got hot.

23:54.991 --> 23:57.580
They went full cage match.
Everyone dies.

23:58.701 --> 24:00.040
Or...

24:00.041 --> 24:01.870
someone got in ahead of time.

24:01.871 --> 24:03.660
Beat the security sweep.

24:03.661 --> 24:05.870
Pulled a surprise move mid-meeting.

24:05.871 --> 24:08.330
[sighs]

24:08.361 --> 24:10.712
Took out the gang bangers first,

24:10.782 --> 24:13.311
most likely to fight back.

24:13.420 --> 24:15.330
Mediator, next.

24:15.331 --> 24:16.700
Former gang member, so...

24:16.701 --> 24:18.001
he was also a threat.

24:21.880 --> 24:23.009
Last,

24:23.064 --> 24:24.415
was our dead mystery body,

24:24.440 --> 24:26.727
'cause who was afraid
of the man in the sweater?

24:27.618 --> 24:30.497
- You forgot the bodyguards.
- Nope.

24:30.498 --> 24:32.407
Bodyguards heard a noise,

24:32.408 --> 24:34.697
- came in...
- [smack]

24:34.698 --> 24:36.021
killer had the advantage.

24:36.046 --> 24:39.237
One person did all that, without
gettin' spotted by anyone?

24:39.238 --> 24:41.037
HARD-ASS 2: Bullshit!

24:41.038 --> 24:44.787
♪ ♪

24:44.788 --> 24:47.201
You get an I.D. on our dead mystery man?

24:47.256 --> 24:48.585
Yeah, prints were on file.

24:48.633 --> 24:49.963
Record?

24:52.868 --> 24:54.077
He owns a liquor store,

24:54.078 --> 24:55.685
so he was printed for his permit.

24:55.710 --> 24:57.169
Name?

24:57.194 --> 24:59.154
CRIME SCENE TECH: Brett LaTour.

25:00.238 --> 25:01.238
[doorbell rings]

25:06.147 --> 25:07.516
I've already spoken to your friends.

25:07.541 --> 25:09.041
Please come back another time.

25:10.572 --> 25:13.291
Uh, now works for me, thanks.

25:19.171 --> 25:20.670
[door closes]

25:20.671 --> 25:23.750
[indistinct chatter]

25:23.751 --> 25:25.670
STEPHANIE LATOUR: Like I
told the other detectives,

25:25.671 --> 25:27.880
I have no idea what
Brett was doing in there.

25:27.881 --> 25:30.250
- He's a businessman, and he...
- And what?

25:30.251 --> 25:32.912
Just wandered into a
gangland summit by accident?

25:32.967 --> 25:35.250
I honestly have no idea.

25:35.251 --> 25:36.630
Well...

25:36.631 --> 25:37.961
you have some idea.

25:40.591 --> 25:42.090
That's a Govinsky, right?

25:42.091 --> 25:44.490
It is. Good eye.

25:44.515 --> 25:46.330
It was a gift...

25:46.367 --> 25:47.576
What the hell are you doing?!

25:47.601 --> 25:49.515
STEPHANIE: That's a $100,000 painting!

25:49.540 --> 25:50.445
- [canvas rips]
- [both gasp]

25:50.470 --> 25:53.150
Owned by a man who declares
$60,000 a year in gross income.

25:53.151 --> 25:55.457
I'm gonna tell Chief Duchamp
about this outrageous behavior.

25:55.482 --> 25:57.020
I'll let you know when I give a shit.

25:57.021 --> 25:59.690
This house was built on dirty
money, I can practically smell it.

25:59.691 --> 26:02.100
Hubby already paid for his sins, so...

26:02.101 --> 26:03.520
who's gonna be next?

26:03.521 --> 26:05.770
Tell me what I need to know,
or I'll go Sotheby's

26:05.771 --> 26:07.771
around this whole goddamn house.

26:14.811 --> 26:16.854
[whispering] One of his businesses

26:16.879 --> 26:19.480
is a salvage yard near
the industrial canal.

26:19.505 --> 26:21.810
Someone's paying him
to store vehicles there.

26:21.856 --> 26:23.715
A lot.

26:23.740 --> 26:24.811
Off the books.

26:24.812 --> 26:26.331
- Stolen cars?
- No.

26:26.356 --> 26:28.190
Nothing stolen.

26:28.191 --> 26:29.760
It was ambulances.

26:29.785 --> 26:31.905
Private ambulances.

26:33.061 --> 26:37.521
♪ ♪

26:40.521 --> 26:42.691
[chains rattling]

26:55.691 --> 26:57.310
You get lost on your way to prom?

26:57.311 --> 26:59.197
What are you doing here?

26:59.222 --> 27:01.052
I'm a cop, I can be wherever I want.

27:02.651 --> 27:04.731
- [gunshot]
- [lock breaks]

27:06.617 --> 27:11.997
WOMAN: [singing]
♪ Far above enthroned in glory ♪

27:13.561 --> 27:20.511
♪ Sweetest Saints of Erin's Isle ♪

27:20.601 --> 27:27.026
♪ See thy children kneel before thee ♪

27:27.151 --> 27:33.881
♪ Turn on us a Mother's smile ♪

27:33.959 --> 27:40.793
♪ Sainted Mother hear our pleadin' ♪

27:41.213 --> 27:47.409
♪ Faith and hope and holy love ♪

27:47.521 --> 27:55.089
♪ Sweet St. Brigid, spouse of Jesus ♪

27:55.151 --> 27:59.066
♪ Sent to us from Heaven above... ♪

27:59.145 --> 28:01.184
I'm not a stalker.

28:01.185 --> 28:03.064
- [singing continues]
- You just seemed really rattled,

28:03.065 --> 28:04.984
and I wanted to make sure you were okay.

28:04.985 --> 28:08.104
- Are all those girls from here?
- ANDRE: Or right nearby.

28:08.105 --> 28:10.434
These folks come together
pretty regular.

28:10.435 --> 28:12.894
To share information,
keep people looking.

28:12.895 --> 28:14.314
To find hope.

28:14.712 --> 28:17.332
That's more than a dozen girls.

28:19.065 --> 28:20.814
Where are the cops?

28:20.815 --> 28:22.984
The reporters? They
should be all over this.

28:22.985 --> 28:24.685
They would be if you went missing.

28:25.654 --> 28:27.568
Pretty blonde girl with
a beautiful white mother

28:27.592 --> 28:29.484
to cry all over the TV?

28:29.485 --> 28:32.266
Breaking news and updates
every few hours.

28:32.565 --> 28:34.595
But here...

28:34.641 --> 28:36.923
where the people in trouble
are poor, brown girls...

28:36.948 --> 28:39.724
- TANDY: That's awful.
- That's the world, Tandy.

28:39.725 --> 28:42.024
Someone has to be looking for them.

28:42.025 --> 28:43.644
Someone is.

28:43.645 --> 28:45.033
These folks right here.

28:45.058 --> 28:47.768
- [singing continues]
- [phone vibrates]

28:50.355 --> 28:51.934
Hey, Lia.

28:51.935 --> 28:53.815
No, we're not at the shelter yet.

28:55.894 --> 28:57.926
Okay, I'll tell Tandy.

28:57.985 --> 28:59.274
She's right here.

28:59.275 --> 29:00.684
Mikayla showed up?

29:00.685 --> 29:02.434
She was found.

29:02.435 --> 29:04.064
Overdosed.

29:04.065 --> 29:05.928
Rushed to Church of All Saints Hospital.

29:05.953 --> 29:07.953
I'll go over with you, if you like.

29:09.777 --> 29:11.639
[panting] Hi...

29:12.065 --> 29:13.392
Lia?

29:13.895 --> 29:15.174
Lia.

29:15.252 --> 29:16.752
She's unconscious, but she's stable.

29:16.799 --> 29:18.642
Doctors don't know when
she's going to wake up.

29:18.667 --> 29:19.956
Do me a favor, when she does...

29:19.994 --> 29:21.914
Don't yell at her, I know.

29:23.985 --> 29:25.702
Sorry.

29:25.757 --> 29:27.934
Seeing one of my girls
shot up so full of heroin

29:27.935 --> 29:29.275
has me on edge.

